text: Eidinemacheilus is a genus of troglobitic fish in the family Nemacheilidae endemic to Iran and Iraqi Kurdistan. ==Species== There are currently 2 recognized species in this genus: * Eidinemacheilus proudlovei Freyhof, Abdullah, Ararat, Ibrahim & Geiger, 2016Freyhof, J., Abdullah, Y.S., Ararat, K., Ibrahim, H. & Geiger, M.F. (2016): Eidinemacheilus proudlovei, a new subterranean loach from Iraqi Kurdistan (Teleostei; Nemacheilidae). Zootaxa, 4173 (3): 225-236. * Eidinemacheilus smithi (Greenwood, 1976) (Zagroz blind loach) ==References== Category:Cave fish Category:Nemacheilidae Category:Fauna of Iran Category:Fauna of Iraq
title: Eidinemacheilus
